{{for|other uses|Battle Arts}} {{spoiler}} [[File:XC3 Noah's Talent Arts.jpg|thumb|240px|Noah using the Swordfighter Talent Art, Overclock Buster]] '''Battle Arts''', or simply '''Arts''' (Japanese: {{lang|ja|アーツ}}, ''Ātsu''), are a battle mechanic in {{XC3}} and {{FR|sublink}}.<ref>[https://topics.nintendo.co.jp/article/a4c0a78d-e993-4fae-8c8e-62c5927040fa Xenoblade Notebook vol. 4: A thorough explanation of the Arts in ''Xenoblade 3''].</ref>
== Overview == They are attacks that can do more damage than a regular attack. They can also heal or buff an ally, and afflict foes with debuffs. All characters and enemies have Battle Arts. Usage of Battle Arts is restricted by a cooldown mechanic that changes depending on the character's [[Class (XC3)|Class]]. For [[Keves]]i classes, once a Battle Art has been used, it normally recharges over time. For [[Agnus|Agnian]] classes, once a Battle Art has been used, it normally recharges by striking an enemy with a certain number of [[Auto-Attack (XC3)|Auto-Attacks]].
== {{XC3|-}} == Arts are assigned to each of the three buttons (BXY buttons) and can be easily used by simply pressing a button. Each character has a variety of standing arts depending on their [[Role]] and Class, and each class has its own unique arts. {{clr}}
=== Talent Arts === [[File:XC3 Talent Arts.jpg|thumb|180px|Icon of an available Talent Art]] Special Arts that can attack more powerfully than normal Arts are called '''Talent Arts''' (Japanese: {{lang|ja|タレントアーツ}}, ''Tarento ātsu''). Talent Arts are accumulated when performing actions that match the character's Role. For example, [[Attacker]]s can easily accumulate Talent Arts by attacking the flanks and backs of enemies with their Arts.
