=== Master Arts === Once a Character has ranked up a Class, the controlled characters can use certain Arts from that class even if they change to another Class. This is called a '''Master Art''' (Japanese: {{lang|ja|マスターアーツ}}, ''Masutā ātsu''). For example, if [[Noah]] uses the Tactician class, he will be able to use some of that class' Arts even if he changes back to [[Swordfighter]]. However, the class of the Master Art cannot be from the same nation as the character's current class. For example, if Noah's current class is Swordfighter, he can only fuse his Swordfighter arts with a Master Art from an [[Agnus]] class.
A Master Art will be automatically unlocked upon unlocking a class and a second Master Art is unlocked upon reaching Rank 10. Upon reaching the maximum rank for a class, that class's Talent Art is unlocked as a Master Art.
While executing a Master Art, the character will temporarily equip the weapon of the original class and assume the class's stats.
The [[Soulhacker]] class cannot use Master Arts, and the only Master Art from the class is its Talent Art.
